(2686, 462, 'about_me_text', 'I\'m a Front-End Web Developer in Vancouver, BC. Inspired to make a change from my career in Tourism, I began my coding journey at BCIT and I was hooked from my first Hello World! I\'ve always enjoyed writing and transferred that knack to computer languages. I appease my adventurous spirit by travelling and experiencing different cultures and cuisines. I enjoy a good trek through a forest, a quality true-crime documentary and spending time with my cats. I\'ve always felt a connection to animals and nature and care deeply about animal welfare and sustainability. I believe that we should always continue learning and pushing ourselves to grow. If it doesn\'t challenge you, it doesn\'t change you and life is all about embracing change.'),
